title: Heavy rain, blustery winds as storm system moves through Puget...
text:
Heavy rain and blustery winds swept through the Puget Sound on Saturday.
A storm system resulted in heavy rain, flooding, downed trees, and mudslide issues in Tacoma.
Storm system
A storm system that moved along the coast Friday night pushed inland Saturday morning.
Rainfall totals across the Sound were expected to be around half an inch.
#WAWX : Storm system moving through #PugetSound —affecting traffic, causing outages >> http://t.co/pGtVLXV3ot pic.twitter.com/WpK5x3A7Ig
— KIRO 7 (@KIRO7Seattle) October 10, 2015 Sunday is expected to be much calmer—with only a few isolated showers and more sun in the mix.
A wind advisory was extended to included most of Western Washington, including the Seattle metro area, throughout Saturday afternoon.
Wind advisory extended to all of Western WA, including the Seattle metro, through this afternoon. #wawx
— NWS Seattle (@NWSSeattle) October 10, 2015
Mudslide, flooding in Tacoma
A mudslide occurred along Schuster Parkway in Tacoma.
No injuries were reported.
Serious flooding along Tacoma roadways prompted Tacoma police officials to simply say: "Tacoma is closed."
Mudslide confirmed in #Tacoma . STORM UPDATES >> http://t.co/pGtVLXV3ot STORM PHOTOS >> http://t.co/8Qp22zZ3aQ pic.twitter.com/XoiB4FW7jp
— KIRO 7 (@KIRO7Seattle) October 10, 2015 A flooding advisory is in effect for parts of Kitsap , Mason , Thurston and Pierce counties -- until 7:15 p.m.
